
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-trill-directory-assist-mechanisms-12.txt'>
    <title>"TRILL: Edge Directory Assist Mechanisms", Donald Eastlake, Linda Dunbar, Radia Perlman, Li Yizhou</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-trill-directory-assist-mechanisms-12.txt</link>
    <description>This document describes mechanisms for providing directory service to TRILL (Transparent Interconnection of Lots of Links) edge switches. The directory information provided can be used in reducing multi- destination traffic, particularly ARP/ND and unknown unicast flooding. It can also be used to detect traffic with forged source addresses.</description>
    <dc:date>2017-03-02T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
